Preheat the #oven to 200°C. Pop the @broccoli florets{200%g} on a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until slightly charred and tender, ~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150%g} and chop into thirds. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Trim the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and sliced thinly) then slice thinly. Trim, then coarsely grate the @carrot{1}(coarsely grated, no need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a glug of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in half the spring onion, the garlic, half the @ginger puree{1}(easy ginger), half the @soy sauce{25%g} and the @rice vinegar{15%ml}. Fry for ~{2%minutes} more.

Add the @brown rice & quinoa{1%portion} and the carrot to the frying pan. Break up any large clumps with a #wooden spoon{}. Cook, stirring occasionally for ~{3%minutes}. Meanwhile, roughly chop the @dried apricots{40%g}. Zest the @lime{1} and cut into quarters.

== Ginger Peanut Dressing ==

Pop the @peanut butter{1%portion} into a small #bowl{}. Mix in the remaining soy sauce and easy ginger and the juice from half the lime. Add the @water{50%ml} and stir well. Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lime juice as needed.

> TIP: You want it to be pouring consistency!

== To Serve ==

Once cooked, add the roasted broccoli to the stir-fry. Stir through the apricots, ginger peanut, coriander and lime zest. Serve in #bowls{} with the peanut butter dressing drizzled all over. Sprinkle over the remaining spring onion and finish with any spare lime wedges popped on the side.